NAME

    plasm - Perl WebAssembly command line tool

VERSION

    version 0.02

SYNOPSIS

     % plasm run program.wasm [ arguments ]
     % plasm dump program.wasm
     % plasm --help
     % plasm --version

    For full documentation:

     % perldoc plasm

DESCRIPTION

    plasm is the Perl WebAssembly command line tool.

SUBCOMMANDS

 run

     % plasm run program.wasm [ arguments ]
     % plasm run --help

    Runs the given WebAssembly program. The arguments after program.wasm
    are passed on to the WebAssembly program.

 dump

     % plasm dump program.wasm
     % plasm dump --help

    Dumps the import and exports of the given WebAssembly module.

 wat

     % plasm wat program.wat
     % plasm wat --help

    Converts WebAssembly Text (.wat) to WebAssembly Binary (.wasm) using
    wasmtime's wat2wasm function.

SEE ALSO

    Wasm

      Write Perl extensions using Wasm!

    Wasm::Wasmtime

      Low-level Wasmtime bindings for Perl.

